The paper discusses the use of deep reinforcement learning (DRL) in autonomous vehicle control systems, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus of the paper is on the security of these systems, which suggests the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the application of DRL in robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV) for autonomous vehicle control.
